result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jennifer L Carter in court with attorney Eric Sheets. Defendant Jennifer L Carter in custody. Louis J. Molepske appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
All files heard: 14CM528, 14CM530, 14CF429, 15CF85, 15CF276, 15CF277
10:56 a.m.  Court calls the cases. 

Court address 14CF429 where the defendant entered an NGI plea.  
Atty Sheets makes statements, will withdraw the NGI plea. 
Court conducts colloquy of defendant. 
Defendant no longer wishes to pursue the NGI plea. 
Atty Molepske makes statements to the Court. 
BY THE COURT:  Court will allow for the withdrawal of the NGI plea. 

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
14CM528 Count 1 - NO CONTEST
14CF429 Counts 1 & 2 - NO CONTEST
15CF276 Counts 1, 2, 3, 6, 7 & 8 - NO CONTEST
15CF277 Count 2 - NO CONTEST


Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

Atty Sheets agrees the defendant qualifies for the repeater enhancer. 

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant is a repeat offender.
Court finds the defendant guilty of the following:
14CM528 Count 1
14CF429 Counts 1 & 2
15CF276 Counts 1, 2, 3, 6, 7 & 8
15CF277 Count 2 
Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Convictions this date.

Dismissed and read-in are the following:
14CF429 Count 3
15CF276 Counts 4, 5 & 9 thru 11
15CF277 Counts 1 & 3 thru 5
14CM530 in its entirety 
15CF85 in its entirety

Atty Molepske makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Sheets makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Molepske makes additional arguments to the Court. 
Defendant makes statements to the Court. 
State has complied with Victim Notification Statutes.

BY THE COURT: 
14CM528 Count 1 - 
Serve 30 days jail. 
163 days credit.
Pay costs. To be paid witin 60 days.  

Atty Molepske makes statements re: jail credit. 
Atty Sheets makes statements re: jail credit. 

14CF429 Count 1 - 
Serve 48 months prison with 24 months Initial Confinement followed by 24 months Extended Supervision, 163 days credit - STAYED-
3 years probation: 
Pay costs. 

14CF429 Count 2 - 
Serve 72 months prison with 36 months Initial Confinement followed by 36 months Extended Supervision, concurrent with Count 1,  - STAYED-
3 years probation: 
Serve 180 days jail.  163 days credit.
No Good time credit. 
Pay restitution on all files:
$1,253.27 joint and several with Jessica Grosskruetz. 
Pay $42.54 restitution to Copps as part of 14CM530 (dismissed and read-in file).
Pay restitution of $7,543.50 in 15CF276.
Pay restitution of $89.84 in 15CF277.
No contact with D.P.C., Jessica Grosskruetz, Cassandra Haessly, Thomas Rivera, Sena Renner. 
Pay costs. 
Conditions of Extended Supervision are those as ordered as probation. 
AODA & comply with treatment recommendations.
Psych evaluation and comply with treatment recommendations which hopefully would include the sexual assault issues.
Maintain fulltime employment. 
Participate in any other assessments including COMPAS and counseling recommended by the agent. 
Write letters of apology to all the victims in these matters. 

15CF276 Counts 1, 2 & 3: 
Serve 60 months prison with 24 months Initial Confinement followed by 3 years Extended Supervision, concurrent with 14CF429 and each count in this file, 163 days credit. - STAYED-
15CF276 Counts 6, 7, & 8:
Serve 66 months prison with 30 months Initial Confinement followed by 36 months Extended Supervision, concurrent with Counts 1, 2, 3 and 14CF429,  163 days credit - STAYED-
3 years probation: 
Same conditions as listed in 14CF429.
Extended Supervision conditions are the same as well. 
Pay costs. 

15CF277 Count 2:
Serve 6 years prison with 36 months Initial Confinement followed by 36 months Extended Supervision concurrent to 15CF276 and 14CF429, 163 days credit - STAYED-
3 years probation: 
Same conditions as in the other files.
Same conditions of extended supervision.  (Not including the 6 months conditional jail time which is only on 14CF429)
Pay costs. 

If revoked, restitution and costs are to be taken out at a rate of 25% of the prison account. 

Eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  Not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program. 

BY THE COURT: 
Credit for 14CM528 - 23 days credit. 
140 days credit on the remaining files. 
Court strikes that.  
Credit of 163 days on each of the files.

Defendant Jennifer L Carter in court with attorney Eric Sheets. Defendant Jennifer L Carter in custody. Louis J. Molepske appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

10:02 a.m.  Court calls case.
Atty Molepske states the appearances.

State files Information.
Defendant received copy of information.
Defendant waives reading of information. 
Case to be Pre-Tried today; report to be filed with the court.
Atty Sheets makes statements regarding the bond on this case and 3 additional files for his client - 14CM528, 14CF429 and 14CM530.
Atty Molepske makes statements regarding the failure of the defendant to appear at day report, this the reason for the cash bond on this case.
State does not have an opposition for change in bond. 
Atty Sheets makes additional statements regarding the cash bond.
Court makes statements that the defendant had failed to appear for day report when out on a signature bond.
Atty Sheets makes statements on 14CM528, 14CF429 and 14CM530 and a cash bond to be imposed on each of these cases with the same conditions. 

BY THE COURT:
NOT GUILTY Plea(s) entered.
Bond Continued.
